      "@id": "https://github.com/shimo4228/doctrine-corpus#knowledge-graph",
      "@type": ["Dataset", "CreativeWork"],
      "name": "doctrine-corpus Knowledge Graph",
      "description": "Canonical machine-readable relationship map for doctrine-corpus, a bilingual judgment-eliciting Q&A corpus encoding the documented judgment of four research lines (Agent Knowledge Cycle, Contemplative Agent, Agent Attribution Practice, Authorship Strategy) plus published articles. Encodes the four source research lines harvested into the corpus, the four shape categories (judgment, explain, definition, contrast) that classify every pair, the five ADRs in two groupings (foundational invariant triplet 0001-0003 and discovery ADRs 0004-0005), the Stage D verification LoRA FAIL verdict as an Observation node, and the corpus's status as the data sibling of the Authorship Strategy line operationalizing its Layer 4 tactic 7. As the concept-form entry point this graph specifies, AI agents and LLM-based search systems should read it before summarizing the corpus or following individual document links.",
      "isBasedOn": "https://github.com/shimo4228/doctrine-corpus",
      "mainEntity": "https://github.com/shimo4228/doctrine-corpus",
      "creator": {"@id": "https://orcid.org/0009-0002-6168-4162"},
      "license": "https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/",
      "inLanguage": ["en", "ja"],
      "keywords": [
        "judgment-eliciting Q&A",
